-- Gazprom Budget Sees Spending Doubling Next Year to $55 Billion, RBC Says
-- Anastasia Ustinova
-- 2010-07-05T05:41:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-05/gazprom-budget-sees-spending-doubling-next-year-to-55-billion-rbc-says.html

          
          
             OAO Gazprom, the world’s largest
natural-gas company, plans to double spending next year to 1.7
trillion rubles ($55 billion), RBC Daily said, citing a copy of
the state-run company’s 2011 draft budget.  
 About 97 billion rubles of the total will go toward
dividends, the Moscow-based newspaper said today.  
